description: Performs Bayes denoising with complete knowledge of sparsity and signal characteristics. Nonzeros of signal iid N(0,1). Sparsity varies from 0.05 to 0.95 in increment of 0.05. Signal rows vary in [100, 200, 400, 600, 800] and 5 columns. Undersampling integer grid half-width 0.1 around the predicted PT value which is max Bayes risk. 25 MC runs per param point.
